{"award_age":84.0,"bio_image":"full\/87c573262d23320f769a03908e81e8e97ceb166a.jpg","category":"Physics","country":"United Kingdom","date_of_birth":"1929-05-29T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/5\/5f\/Nobel_Prize_24_2013.jpg\/220px-Nobel_Prize_24_2013.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs","mini_bio":"<p><b>Peter Ware Higgs<\/b> <small style=\"font-size:85%;\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Companion_of_Honour\" title=\"Companion of Honour\" class=\"mw-redirect\">CH<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society\" title=\"Fellow of the Royal Society\" class=\"mw-redirect\">FRS<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society_of_Edinburgh\" title=\"Fellow of the Royal Society of Edinburgh\" class=\"mw-redirect\">FRSE<\/a><\/small> (born 29 May 1929) is a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/British_people\" title=\"British people\">British<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Theoretical_physics\" title=\"Theoretical physics\">theoretical physicist<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Emeritus_professor\" title=\"Emeritus professor\" class=\"mw-redirect\">emeritus professor<\/a> at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Edinburgh\" title=\"University of Edinburgh\">University of Edinburgh<\/a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Edit_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-Edit-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT-20140915_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-NYT-20140915-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup>and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physics\">Nobel Prize<\/a> laureate \"for the theoretical discovery of a mechanism that contributes to our understanding of the origin of mass of subatomic particles\".<\/p><p>He is best known for his 1960s proposal of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Broken_symmetry\" title=\"Broken symmetry\" class=\"mw-redirect\">broken symmetry<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Electroweak_theory\" title=\"Electroweak theory\" class=\"mw-redirect\">electroweak theory<\/a>, explaining the origin of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Mass\" title=\"Mass\">mass<\/a> of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Elementary_particles\" title=\"Elementary particles\" class=\"mw-redirect\">elementary particles<\/a> in general and of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/W_and_Z_bosons\" title=\"W and Z bosons\">W and Z bosons<\/a> in particular. This so-called <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Higgs_mechanism\" title=\"Higgs mechanism\">Higgs mechanism<\/a>, which was proposed by several physicists besides Higgs at about the same time, predicts the existence of a new particle, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Higgs_boson\" title=\"Higgs boson\">Higgs boson<\/a> (which was often described as \"the most sought-after particle in modern physics\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup>). <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/CERN\" title=\"CERN\">CERN<\/a> announced on 4 July 2012 that they had experimentally established the existence of a Higgs-like boson,<sup id=\"cite_ref-BBC-04Jul12_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-BBC-04Jul12-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> but further work is needed to analyse its properties and see whether it has the properties expected from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Standard_Model\" title=\"Standard Model\">Standard Model<\/a> Higgs boson.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> On 14 March 2013, the newly discovered particle was tentatively confirmed to be + parity and zero spin,<sup id=\"cite_ref-CERN_March_2013_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-CERN_March_2013-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> two fundamental criteria of a Higgs boson, making it the first known fundamental <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Scalar_boson\" title=\"Scalar boson\">scalar particle<\/a> to be discovered in nature (although previously, composite scalars<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> such as the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Scalar_meson\" title=\"Scalar meson\">K*<\/a> had been observed over half a century prior).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WSJ_14_March_2013_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-WSJ_14_March_2013-11\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> The Higgs mechanism is generally accepted as an important ingredient in the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Standard_Model\" title=\"Standard Model\">Standard Model<\/a> of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Particle_physics\" title=\"Particle physics\">particle physics<\/a>, without which certain particles would have no mass.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-12\"><span>[<\/span>12<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Higgs has been honoured with a number of awards in recognition of his work, including the 1981 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Hughes_Medal\" title=\"Hughes Medal\">Hughes Medal<\/a> from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Royal_Society\" title=\"Royal Society\">Royal Society<\/a>; the 1984 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Rutherford_Medal_and_Prize\" title=\"Rutherford Medal and Prize\">Rutherford Medal<\/a> from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Institute_of_Physics\" title=\"Institute of Physics\">Institute of Physics<\/a>; the 1997 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dirac_Medal\" title=\"Dirac Medal\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Dirac Medal<\/a> and Prize for outstanding contributions to theoretical physics from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Institute_of_Physics\" title=\"Institute of Physics\">Institute of Physics<\/a>; the 1997 High Energy and Particle Physics Prize by the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/European_Physical_Society\" title=\"European Physical Society\">European Physical Society<\/a>; the 2004 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wolf_Prize_in_Physics\" title=\"Wolf Prize in Physics\">Wolf Prize in Physics<\/a>; the 2009 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Oskar_Klein_Memorial_Lecture\" title=\"Oskar Klein Memorial Lecture\">Oskar Klein Memorial Lecture<\/a> medal from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Royal_Swedish_Academy_of_Sciences\" title=\"Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences\">Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences<\/a>; the 2010 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/American_Physical_Society\" title=\"American Physical Society\">American Physical Society<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sakurai_Prize\" title=\"Sakurai Prize\">J. J. Sakurai Prize for Theoretical Particle Physics<\/a>; and a unique Higgs Medal from the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Royal_Society_of_Edinburgh\" title=\"Royal Society of Edinburgh\">Royal Society of Edinburgh<\/a> in 2012.<sup id=\"cite_ref-CV_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-CV-13\"><span>[<\/span>13<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> The recent potential discovery of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Higgs_boson\" title=\"Higgs boson\">Higgs boson<\/a> prompted fellow physicist <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Stephen_Hawking\" title=\"Stephen Hawking\">Stephen Hawking<\/a> to note that he thought that Higgs should receive the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physics\">Nobel Prize in Physics<\/a> for his work,<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-14\"><span>[<\/span>14<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-15\"><span>[<\/span>15<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> which he finally did, shared with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fran%C3%A7ois_Englert\" title=\"Fran\u00e7ois Englert\">Fran\u00e7ois Englert<\/a> in 2013.<sup id=\"cite_ref-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-16\"><span>[<\/span>16<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Higgs was appointed to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_the_Companions_of_Honour\" title=\"Order of the Companions of Honour\">Order of the Companions of Honour<\/a> in the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/2013_New_Year_Honours\" title=\"2013 New Year Honours\">2013 New Year Honours<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-17\"><span>[<\/span>17<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-18\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peter_Higgs#cite_note-18\"><span>[<\/span>18<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Peter Higgs","place_of_birth":"Newcastle upon Tyne, England, UK","place_of_death":null,"text":"Peter Higgs , Physics, 2013","year":2013.0}